t their opting out processes. In addition, Biese explores what organizations can learn from the knowledge gathered in her research on men (and women) opting out. This is important in order to create sustainable work environments that not only attract but also retain employees.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 4aKarriere. 4aMaskulinitäten. 4aMänner. 4aNachhaltige Lebensstile. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh  aCareer.  aMasculinities.  aMen.  aOpting Out.  aSustainable Lifestyles.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package 2021z978311075070608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package English 2021z978311075072008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishz978311075418608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021z9783110753967oZDB-23-DSW0 cEPUBz97831107259020 cprintz978311072416540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110725797423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110725797.jpg  a978-3-11-075070-6  DG Ebook Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075072-0  DG Ebook Package English 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075418-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  aZDB-23-DSWb2021